reviews.review_text:
Magnicent Betty Board A sound so regal and firmly underpinned, it is simply too much bass recorded to handle most home systems. Probably have to EQ the bass flat.

And perhaps not the band's best showing, but the recording/remastering make up for it. Would imagine one could hook this up to the Wall of Sound, have the band stand on stage and lip-synch.

There is some scratchy distortion in Estimated -- have a hunch it's Jerry's refurbished Wolf kinda kicking out its newness.

The separation and clarity of each instrument audible on this stream is uncanny.

I want to tell you , how it's gonna be.. Perspective
This is NOT a traditional mix and it kinda reminds me
of seeing a really good GD cover band
except this is Fall 77

It takes me til Passenger to settle in.
Donna & Bob with the going for it vocals
and the best Garcia riffs of the night (so far)
SMOKIN' PASSENGER!
Jed , can really hear the band grinding it out
 Keith is very prominent 
also the drums are full on.
Me thinks there is a lot of Weir.
and Phil is over and below the drummers rhythm 
Peggy O sounds distant in this mix
but focusing less on Garcia's vocals
and just enjoying the rest of the band being introspective
Weir's vocals low to start on Music but the rhythm section.
Everything in proper alignment for the Music jam🎩 Dang.

Try to outdance this BERTHA
(Not for the faint of heart)
and GOOD Lovin' is double timing and quick steppin'
The ROSES-same feel as Peggy O just even mellower 
Estimated>Eyes feelin good standard 77
but really like the EYES outro
Phil in the lead.
were u heading to the fridge?
expecting da drummers
Not so fast
unscheduled Dancin'
Picks up where the MNS jam left off and then some..
You kinda gotta stick with this show
but it has the goods
all the nooks and crannies
payoff when they let loose.
some cool sound for drums
very intricate..
NFA with an Aiko backbeat
Not Fade in 77 packs a punch.
Almost a Prof. Longhair shimmy
The NFA jam is hot here
perhaps Donna slam dancing at this point,  
3rd really tight jam of the night and then back to the NFA lyrics.
Black Peter-finest of the Garcia ballads this night
everybody dripping, Jerry breaths into the vocals.
Donna adds sweetness to Shine thru my window..
AROUND- perfect nightcap for this rockin' freewheelin show
and yes that AROUND jam is peaking and FREAKIN'
and even hinting at the JBG encore 10/2/77.
WOW!
